Sixth limb (
Fig. 3
J;
Table 3
). The sixth limb is very different. Its basale carries two proximal setae and one distal, very short on ventral margin. First and second endopodite segments are bare, third segment has three long terminal setae, all similar in length, 49.6 % ± 3.4 % CL, and carry long fine hairs terminally.

Copulatory appendage (
Fig. 3
L;
Table 3
). The appendage is characteristically shaped. Its length is 19.1 % ± 1.6 % CL and width 4.5 % ± 0.8 % CL. It has five oblique muscles and its tip is rounded.
